WEBVTT

00:00:01.635 --> 00:00:04.104
(Ai)
<i>Previously on
"Yu-Gi-Oh! VRAINS"...</i>

00:00:05.472 --> 00:00:08.308
I didn't expect The Gore
to turn me down,

00:00:08.341 --> 00:00:11.579
but I'll just have to approach
the next best duelist.

00:00:11.645 --> 00:00:15.415
Now, I need to find someone
to defeat Playmaker...

00:00:15.482 --> 00:00:17.417
(Gore)
You already did, Zaizen.

00:00:17.484 --> 00:00:20.587
(Zaizen)
I appreciate that
you've changed your mind.

00:00:20.654 --> 00:00:22.656
You know what I want, Gore.

00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:26.326
Defeat Playmaker
and bring his Ignis to me.

00:00:26.426 --> 00:00:28.428
Let's Speed Duel!
Let's Speed Duel!

00:00:29.963 --> 00:00:32.632
Linkslayer,
attack Gouki Suprex!

00:00:35.469 --> 00:00:37.304
(groans)

00:00:43.076 --> 00:00:44.945
<i>The Gore donates
all his winnings</i>

00:00:44.978 --> 00:00:47.247
<i>to an orphanage,
every last penny.</i>

00:00:47.314 --> 00:00:49.283
<i>Even though his own gym
could use an upgrade.</i>

00:00:49.316 --> 00:00:52.152
<i>The more popular he became,
the more he earned.</i>

00:00:52.252 --> 00:00:54.821
<i>So it's not an ego thing
that he needs to stay famous.</i>

00:00:54.921 --> 00:00:58.092
<i>He's actually a sweet,
caring softy like me!</i>

00:00:58.158 --> 00:01:01.161
(Emcee)
<i>I can't believe
what I'm seeing!</i>

00:01:01.228 --> 00:01:02.496
<i>The Gore's back on his feet!</i>

00:01:02.562 --> 00:01:03.931
<i>Wow!</i>

00:01:04.031 --> 00:01:05.399
(Gore)
I Link Summon!

00:01:05.499 --> 00:01:09.402
Link 3,
Gouki The Great Ogre!

00:01:09.502 --> 00:01:12.205
The Gore's about to steamroll
Yusaku big time.

00:01:12.239 --> 00:01:13.374
This isn't good.

00:01:13.407 --> 00:01:16.176
I gotta get Yusaku
outta there fast!

00:01:16.209 --> 00:01:19.380
Great Ogre,
hit 'em with your finisher!

00:01:19.480 --> 00:01:21.147
(Gore cackling)

00:01:24.318 --> 00:01:27.320
♪♪♪

00:02:25.446 --> 00:02:27.548
(snarling)

00:02:27.615 --> 00:02:28.882
<i>Aww, glitch!</i>

00:02:28.949 --> 00:02:30.484
<i>That hairy brute's
gonna shred us!</i>

00:02:30.584 --> 00:02:32.786
Must you always panic?

00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:36.290
I activate
the trap Cyberse Shatter!

00:02:36.323 --> 00:02:39.593
It negates Gouki Headbatt's
special ability,

00:02:39.627 --> 00:02:42.462
dropping The Great Ogre's
attack points by 800.

00:02:44.731 --> 00:02:47.134
Plus, I can now draw one card.

00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:48.268
<i>What?</i>

00:02:48.302 --> 00:02:49.937
<i>If you had that card
laying around,</i>

00:02:49.970 --> 00:02:52.139
<i>why didn't you use it earlier
on Twistcobra?</i>

00:02:52.239 --> 00:02:55.108
<i>It woulda prevented more damage
and we'd be in less trouble!</i>

00:02:57.111 --> 00:02:59.613
(Gore's AI)
<i>Your attack no longer
guarantees victory.</i>

00:02:59.713 --> 00:03:02.048
<i>Playmaker will have
100 life points left.</i>

00:03:02.148 --> 00:03:05.018
So what? Even if we don't
finish the guy right now,

00:03:05.052 --> 00:03:06.654
he'll barely have
a pulse left!

00:03:06.687 --> 00:03:09.356
Gouki The Great Ogre,
attack Cyberse Wizard

00:03:09.457 --> 00:03:11.291
and eliminate him
once and for all!

00:03:13.126 --> 00:03:15.028
Blast 'im with your Ogre Axe!

00:03:15.061 --> 00:03:17.030
♪♪♪

00:03:19.466 --> 00:03:20.901
<i>(whimpering)</i>

00:03:28.675 --> 00:03:31.111
Looks like it's your turn,
Playmaker.

00:03:31.178 --> 00:03:33.179
(fans cheering)
Yeah, yeah!

00:03:38.118 --> 00:03:39.353
Unbelievable !

00:03:39.453 --> 00:03:41.354
Just when we thought The Gore
had one of his ginormous

00:03:41.454 --> 00:03:43.290
size sixteens in the grave,

00:03:43.356 --> 00:03:46.126
<i>Playmaker's the one
on life support!</i>

00:03:46.193 --> 00:03:49.063
<i>He's gonna to need
some CPR for his CPU</i>

00:03:49.163 --> 00:03:51.732
<i>if he doesn't
turn things around!</i>

00:03:51.832 --> 00:03:54.701
Come on, Gore,
smash and bash
and gnash and thrash!

00:03:54.801 --> 00:03:57.171
Gore has the scariest
and hairiest monsters!

00:03:57.204 --> 00:03:59.506
If they're cheering
this loud for George now,

00:03:59.606 --> 00:04:02.243
it'll be completely off
the charts when he wins.

00:04:02.276 --> 00:04:03.944
Oh, he will.

00:04:04.044 --> 00:04:07.948
(Manager)
After all, Playmaker only has
a hundred life points left,

00:04:08.048 --> 00:04:11.352
but I'll breath a lot easier
when he's down to zero.

00:04:11.418 --> 00:04:13.787
♪♪♪

00:04:13.887 --> 00:04:16.190
Good, now finish
Playmaker off

00:04:16.257 --> 00:04:18.259
and bring his Ignis
directly to me!

00:04:18.359 --> 00:04:20.528
Install this patch and... Bam!

00:04:20.594 --> 00:04:22.362
Kolter does it again!

00:04:22.429 --> 00:04:24.965
Yusaku's escape route
is online!

00:04:25.065 --> 00:04:27.868
Playmaker! Take five
from hangin' ten

00:04:27.902 --> 00:04:30.204
and get your butt
back in this pen!

00:04:30.237 --> 00:04:32.072
♪♪♪

00:04:36.010 --> 00:04:37.911
(Ai)
<i>Oh, bonus!</i>

00:04:37.945 --> 00:04:39.913
<i>Playmaker,
it's your lucky break!</i>

00:04:39.947 --> 00:04:41.748
<i>There's a security
bypass ahead!</i>

00:04:41.781 --> 00:04:43.784
<i>We can log out of
Link VRAINS from there!</i>

00:04:43.884 --> 00:04:45.285
Hmm?

00:04:49.756 --> 00:04:51.424
<i>Home sweet ho...</i>

00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:55.262
<i>Uhh... Umm... U-Turn?</i>

00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:58.732
I'm not logging out
of Link VRAINS just yet.

00:04:58.765 --> 00:05:01.268
How in the world do you miss
a target that big?

00:05:03.270 --> 00:05:04.738
<i>That's it!
Your motherboard's</i>

00:05:04.805 --> 00:05:06.640
<i>officially glitched
beyond repair!</i>

00:05:06.740 --> 00:05:09.143
<i>Ya mind explaining why
you zigged instead of zagged?</i>

00:05:09.176 --> 00:05:10.744
I could've logged out,

00:05:10.810 --> 00:05:13.247
but there are three
good reasons why I didn't.

00:05:13.313 --> 00:05:15.416
First,
the Gore is presenting me

00:05:15.483 --> 00:05:16.817
with unexpected strategies
and techniques,

00:05:16.917 --> 00:05:19.487
moves and techniques
that I am able learn from

00:05:19.520 --> 00:05:21.188
to improve my own dueling.

00:05:21.288 --> 00:05:23.991
Second, continuing this duel
may provide insight

00:05:24.091 --> 00:05:26.527
as to who would go to such
lengths to trap us here

00:05:26.627 --> 00:05:28.862
inside this quantum cage
for the sole purpose

00:05:28.962 --> 00:05:30.497
of acquiring you, Ai.

00:05:30.597 --> 00:05:32.499
And third,
I'm choosing to continue

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:34.301
this battle with Gore
and not log out

00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:35.969
because I feel like it.

00:05:36.002 --> 00:05:38.438
<i>After listening to you,
my mind needs a reboot!</i>

00:05:38.472 --> 00:05:39.773
It's my turn!

00:05:39.806 --> 00:05:42.342
I draw!

00:05:42.442 --> 00:05:44.844
To start,
I'll summon Draconnet!

00:05:47.847 --> 00:05:50.750
I'm now going to activate
Draconnet's special ability

00:05:50.817 --> 00:05:53.354
which allows me to summon
a monster straight from my deck

00:05:53.454 --> 00:05:55.288
that's level two or below
in defense mode.

00:05:55.322 --> 00:05:56.990
Join us, Bitron!

00:06:01.262 --> 00:06:02.729
Big deal!

00:06:02.763 --> 00:06:05.932
My Great Ogre wipes out
all its attack points!

00:06:06.032 --> 00:06:07.500
(whimpering)

00:06:09.035 --> 00:06:11.371
<i>Nice, another monster
that can't attack.</i>

00:06:11.405 --> 00:06:13.841
True, but I was never
planning to attack.

00:06:13.874 --> 00:06:17.244
<i>What? Then why'd you
summon that pipsqueak?</i>

00:06:17.344 --> 00:06:18.578
To do this!

00:06:18.678 --> 00:06:20.347
Create my ultimate circuit!

00:06:26.220 --> 00:06:28.221
♪♪♪

00:06:32.693 --> 00:06:34.561
Link Arrows authorized!

00:06:34.595 --> 00:06:38.198
I require one monster
in order to Link Summon!

00:06:38.231 --> 00:06:40.734
So I set Bitron
in the Link Arrow!

00:06:44.204 --> 00:06:46.407
Link the circuit!

00:06:46.507 --> 00:06:47.908
I Link Summon...

00:06:48.008 --> 00:06:50.176
Link 1 Link Spider!

00:06:57.851 --> 00:07:00.020
Spin your web, Link Spider!

00:07:00.054 --> 00:07:03.290
It summons a monster
that's Level 4 or below

00:07:03.323 --> 00:07:04.658
right next to its arrow!

00:07:07.127 --> 00:07:08.562
Rise, Bitron!

00:07:11.565 --> 00:07:12.966
(cackling)

00:07:13.066 --> 00:07:15.569
You seriously for real playing
that little fella again?

00:07:15.602 --> 00:07:17.938
Now you're just straight up
trying to ruin my cred!

00:07:17.972 --> 00:07:19.573
'Cause if I pound
that powder puff,

00:07:19.606 --> 00:07:21.408
the kids'll think
I'm the heel!

00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:24.745
<i>Well, he's sure crushing us
under his, Playmaker!</i>

00:07:24.778 --> 00:07:27.113
<i>But no, you don't
need my help.</i>

00:07:27.147 --> 00:07:28.615
<i>You're fine.</i>

00:07:28.716 --> 00:07:30.116
<i>You think a miracle
will save you?</i>

00:07:30.150 --> 00:07:32.486
Of course not.
<i>(Ai gasps)</i>

00:07:32.586 --> 00:07:35.989
I have no need for miracles
when I have skill.

00:07:36.089 --> 00:07:37.958
And it guides me there!

00:07:38.058 --> 00:07:39.559
♪♪♪

00:07:42.930 --> 00:07:45.933
I have no need for miracles
when I have skill.

00:07:45.966 --> 00:07:47.801
And it guides me there!

00:07:50.236 --> 00:07:52.606
Huh? Whatcha talkin'
about skill?

00:07:52.706 --> 00:07:55.242
(Gore's AI)
<i>Playmaker possesses a skill
that he can activate</i>

00:07:55.275 --> 00:07:58.379
<i>when he has one thousand
or fewer life points.</i>

00:07:58.445 --> 00:08:01.482
Are you tellin' me that
this jobber took 3,900 points

00:08:01.515 --> 00:08:02.882
of damage on purpose?

00:08:02.983 --> 00:08:04.852
<i>All signs point
to affirmative.</i>

00:08:04.952 --> 00:08:06.787
He worked me!

00:08:06.854 --> 00:08:08.789
But that don't change a thing!

00:08:08.856 --> 00:08:11.959
With just a hundred life points,
he's like a flickering candle,

00:08:12.026 --> 00:08:14.027
and that storm'll blow him out!

00:08:17.531 --> 00:08:19.633
♪♪♪

00:08:33.947 --> 00:08:36.149
<i>Seize the wind, Playmaker!</i>

00:08:38.352 --> 00:08:39.853
(grunting)

00:08:51.064 --> 00:08:53.366
Go storm access!

00:09:02.743 --> 00:09:05.412
So like, what punk card did ya
draw out of the Data Storm?

00:09:05.446 --> 00:09:08.114
Don't worry, I won't keep you
in suspense.

00:09:09.616 --> 00:09:12.953
I Link Summon
for a second time!

00:09:16.557 --> 00:09:18.458
♪♪♪

00:09:24.965 --> 00:09:26.867
Link arrows authorized!

00:09:26.933 --> 00:09:28.669
This time,
the summoning conditions

00:09:28.736 --> 00:09:30.671
are two Cyberse Monsters.

00:09:30.738 --> 00:09:34.908
So I set my Bitron and my
Linkslayer in the Link Arrows!

00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:39.746
Link the circuit!

00:09:41.348 --> 00:09:42.750
I Link Summon!

00:09:42.850 --> 00:09:45.219
Link 2, Link Bumper!

00:09:45.252 --> 00:09:47.587
♪♪♪

00:09:54.861 --> 00:09:57.965
When I have a Cyberse monster
on my field,

00:09:58.065 --> 00:10:01.034
I can automatically summon
Backup Secretary!

00:10:04.237 --> 00:10:07.074
Which then allows me to
Link Summon for a third time!

00:10:07.174 --> 00:10:09.109
Go!
(gasps)

00:10:09.209 --> 00:10:10.877
♪♪♪

00:10:17.785 --> 00:10:19.453
This is it.

00:10:19.553 --> 00:10:22.923
I require two Cyberse monsters
to Link Summon.

00:10:22.957 --> 00:10:25.926
And so I set my Backup Secretary

00:10:25.959 --> 00:10:28.295
and my Draconnet
in the Link Arrows!

00:10:31.198 --> 00:10:33.533
Link the circuit again!

00:10:35.502 --> 00:10:36.837
I Link Summon...

00:10:36.904 --> 00:10:38.238
Link 2 Honeybot!

00:10:39.874 --> 00:10:42.075
There's more!
No way!

00:10:46.246 --> 00:10:48.449
My quadruple Link Summon!

00:10:48.549 --> 00:10:51.952
I'm required to have at least
two Effect Monsters this time.

00:10:52.052 --> 00:10:55.756
So I set Link 2 Honeybot
and Link 1 Link Spider

00:10:55.789 --> 00:10:57.624
in the Link Arrows!

00:11:01.695 --> 00:11:04.097
Link the circuit
for a final time!

00:11:10.937 --> 00:11:12.339
I Link Summon!

00:11:12.439 --> 00:11:14.675
And bring forth my Link 3...

00:11:14.775 --> 00:11:16.276
Decode talker!

00:11:22.249 --> 00:11:25.653
(Playmaker)
I Link Summon!
And bring forth my Link 3...

00:11:25.753 --> 00:11:27.587
Decode talker!

00:11:29.089 --> 00:11:30.323
You know what, folks?

00:11:30.423 --> 00:11:31.825
You'd need a roll of pennies

00:11:31.925 --> 00:11:33.594
to witness more
linkin' than this!

00:11:33.660 --> 00:11:35.662
Way to go, Playmaker!

00:11:37.832 --> 00:11:42.069
I'm equip my Decode Talker with
the spell Cyberse Annihilation.

00:11:42.135 --> 00:11:44.571
♪♪♪

00:11:48.075 --> 00:11:50.477
Then I activate
Cyberse Shatter's effect

00:11:50.510 --> 00:11:52.813
by banishing it
from my graveyard.

00:11:52.846 --> 00:11:55.782
That way I can Summon a Cyberse
that's Link 2 or less

00:11:55.816 --> 00:11:57.117
from my graveyard.

00:11:57.151 --> 00:11:58.585
Return, Honeybot!

00:12:06.060 --> 00:12:08.996
That's a whole lot of labor
for a whole lot of nothing!

00:12:09.062 --> 00:12:11.398
Not one of those weaklings
is strong enough

00:12:11.431 --> 00:12:13.233
to defeat The Great Ogre!

00:12:13.267 --> 00:12:15.902
Really now?
My Monsters are more

00:12:16.002 --> 00:12:17.404
of a threat than you think.

00:12:17.504 --> 00:12:20.874
Attack, Decode Talker!

00:12:20.975 --> 00:12:24.044
Why are you attacking with a
Monster that's weaker than mine?

00:12:24.077 --> 00:12:27.548
(Playmaker)
Decode Talker isn't weaker,
because I equipped it

00:12:27.581 --> 00:12:29.049
with Cyberse Annihilation,

00:12:29.082 --> 00:12:32.052
which raises its attack points
to match The Great Ogre's!

00:12:32.152 --> 00:12:33.820
Your monster's destroyed!

00:12:34.988 --> 00:12:36.890
Yours too, punk!

00:12:36.924 --> 00:12:38.258
(metal clanging)

00:12:46.700 --> 00:12:51.071
(Emcee)
<i>Whoa! Are you kidding me?</i>

00:12:51.172 --> 00:12:54.841
<i>Both monsters are out cold
and I don't think either one</i>

00:12:54.875 --> 00:12:56.209
<i>is getting up!</i>

00:13:01.615 --> 00:13:02.949
Aww, man.

00:13:02.983 --> 00:13:06.419
Looks like both of
their best monsters are goners.

00:13:06.453 --> 00:13:08.922
Or... maybe not?

00:13:16.296 --> 00:13:18.799
Why's your Monster
still alive and kickin'?

00:13:18.832 --> 00:13:20.634
Because of Honeybot.

00:13:20.668 --> 00:13:23.704
Her special ability
prevents Decode Talker

00:13:23.771 --> 00:13:25.438
from being destroyed in battle.

00:13:30.778 --> 00:13:33.280
My Monster's back on its feet!
(roaring)

00:13:34.448 --> 00:13:37.284
So that curtain jerker's
a tough guy, huh?

00:13:38.619 --> 00:13:41.589
Well, my Ogre's tough, too!

00:13:41.622 --> 00:13:43.958
Use your special ability!

00:13:44.058 --> 00:13:46.560
By destroying a monster
that's linked to it,

00:13:46.627 --> 00:13:48.962
The Great Ogre rises
to fight again!

00:13:55.201 --> 00:13:58.939
And When Headbatt's gone,
its special ability lets me

00:13:59.040 --> 00:14:01.608
add a Gouki card
in my deck to my hand.

00:14:03.277 --> 00:14:05.378
Like that?

00:14:05.478 --> 00:14:08.181
(Emcee)
<i>Oh, oh, oh, my!</i>

00:14:08.215 --> 00:14:11.285
<i>This mesmerizing main event
has yours truly wondering</i>

00:14:11.351 --> 00:14:13.854
<i>whose finisher is gonna
finish this duel!</i>

00:14:13.954 --> 00:14:16.523
<i>Who will break who first?</i>

00:14:19.526 --> 00:14:20.895
♪♪♪

00:14:20.995 --> 00:14:24.365
Your weak sauce alliance
sure botched up that finish.

00:14:24.465 --> 00:14:27.334
And who said
that I was finished?

00:14:27.368 --> 00:14:28.802
Say what?

00:14:28.835 --> 00:14:33.106
Link Bumper, activate your
ability and give Decode Talker

00:14:33.173 --> 00:14:36.509
an extra attack for every other
Link Monster that I have!

00:14:38.178 --> 00:14:41.682
Decode Talker, attack Gouki
The Great Ogre once again!

00:14:41.782 --> 00:14:44.117
You know the outcome
will be the same.

00:14:44.184 --> 00:14:47.187
Yeah, then that means
this shouldn't worry you.

00:14:47.287 --> 00:14:50.691
Cyberse Annihilation once again
raises Decode Talker's

00:14:50.791 --> 00:14:54.194
attack points to match
The Great Ogre's.

00:14:57.197 --> 00:14:58.865
Go!
Time for Round Two!

00:14:58.965 --> 00:15:00.734
Strike that chump down!

00:15:02.035 --> 00:15:03.670
(both grunting)

00:15:19.519 --> 00:15:22.422
(Emcee)
<i>Another double K.O.!</i>

00:15:22.455 --> 00:15:24.124
♪♪♪

00:15:24.224 --> 00:15:25.926
(gasps)

00:15:29.430 --> 00:15:32.599
Since Twistcobra's linked
to The Great Ogre,

00:15:32.699 --> 00:15:35.068
I can destroy it to keep
my main man in the match!

00:15:37.070 --> 00:15:41.408
Likewise, my Honeybot protects
Decode Talker from destruction.

00:15:44.011 --> 00:15:45.745
(roaring)

00:15:47.948 --> 00:15:50.251
Since I destroyed Twistcobra,

00:15:50.284 --> 00:15:52.720
its special ability
kicks in big time!

00:15:52.753 --> 00:15:54.422
I get to draw Gouki Suprex

00:15:54.522 --> 00:15:57.090
which'll come in
really handy next turn...

00:15:57.190 --> 00:15:58.125
To beat you!

00:15:58.225 --> 00:15:59.793
There won't be a next turn!

00:15:59.893 --> 00:16:02.195
Link Bumper,
use your ability!

00:16:03.497 --> 00:16:07.367
Decode Talker
gets one final attack!

00:16:07.468 --> 00:16:10.337
It all comes down
to this fight, Gore!

00:16:10.438 --> 00:16:14.307
Cyberse Annihilation, raise
Decode Talker's attack points!

00:16:14.407 --> 00:16:17.410
♪♪♪

00:16:23.150 --> 00:16:25.485
Attack The Great Ogre!

00:16:25.585 --> 00:16:27.487
♪♪♪

00:16:27.521 --> 00:16:29.789
Ogre! Smash 'em!

00:16:36.130 --> 00:16:38.164
(Monsters growling)

00:16:40.834 --> 00:16:42.135
(sword slicing)

00:16:53.147 --> 00:16:54.982
(Playmaker)
My monster's still standing.

00:16:55.082 --> 00:16:57.083
Yours however, is not.

00:16:57.150 --> 00:17:00.253
Yeah? The Great Ogre will
kip up in no time!

00:17:00.320 --> 00:17:02.989
All I gotta do is destroy
another one of my monsters

00:17:03.056 --> 00:17:04.591
that it's linked to
which'll be...

00:17:04.691 --> 00:17:06.526
(gasps)
Oh, no!

00:17:08.662 --> 00:17:11.064
I'm afraid you've run out
of Monsters, Gore.

00:17:13.066 --> 00:17:16.670
That means you can't save
The Great Ogre anymore!

00:17:16.703 --> 00:17:18.639
Huh?

00:17:18.705 --> 00:17:20.707
♪♪♪

00:17:24.645 --> 00:17:26.046
(crowd murmuring)

00:17:26.080 --> 00:17:27.547
(children gasping)

00:17:33.053 --> 00:17:35.656
And when your monster is
destroyed in battle...

00:17:35.722 --> 00:17:38.592
Cyberse Annihilation deals
you damage equal to

00:17:38.692 --> 00:17:40.260
your monster's attack points,

00:17:40.360 --> 00:17:42.362
which is more than enough
to defeat you.

00:17:47.067 --> 00:17:48.368
(groaning)

00:17:52.505 --> 00:17:54.875
(bell ringing)

00:17:54.975 --> 00:17:56.209
Oh, yeah!

00:17:56.309 --> 00:17:58.379
The Gore is down
for the three count!

00:17:58.412 --> 00:18:02.282
<i>He met his maker, Playmaker,
in a duel to the finish!</i>

00:18:02.316 --> 00:18:05.386
(children crying)

00:18:05.452 --> 00:18:08.388
♪♪♪

00:18:21.735 --> 00:18:24.137
(cackling)

00:18:24.238 --> 00:18:26.239
That was amazing!

00:18:29.143 --> 00:18:31.979
(Ai)
<i>Um, who laughs after
they lose a duel?</i>

00:18:32.079 --> 00:18:33.613
<i>His eyes should
be dripping with water</i>

00:18:33.647 --> 00:18:34.882
<i>as if his tear ducts broke!</i>

00:18:34.948 --> 00:18:38.151
Why would he need to mourn after
a well-fought fight, Ai?

00:18:38.251 --> 00:18:40.287
There's no shame in losing.

00:18:40.387 --> 00:18:41.922
<i>Of course there is!</i>

00:18:41.955 --> 00:18:43.790
<i>You humans are weird.</i>

00:18:52.098 --> 00:18:54.702
It wasn't easy
programming that exit.

00:18:54.769 --> 00:18:56.203
Yes. But you know,

00:18:56.270 --> 00:18:57.638
it's not every day
that I get to duel

00:18:57.738 --> 00:18:59.640
just for the sake of dueling.

00:18:59.740 --> 00:19:02.376
Well, I guess you're right.

00:19:02.476 --> 00:19:05.679
That Gore was pretty good,
wasn't he?

00:19:05.779 --> 00:19:07.815
You know what?

00:19:07.848 --> 00:19:11.118
If we really are going to take
down the Knights of Hanoi,

00:19:11.184 --> 00:19:13.454
then we should try to get
all the help we can get.

00:19:13.520 --> 00:19:16.623
We could use an ally
like The Gore.

00:19:16.690 --> 00:19:20.394
No.
It's too dangerous.

00:19:20.494 --> 00:19:22.062
This is our fight, Kolter.

00:19:22.162 --> 00:19:24.064
Not his.

00:19:24.164 --> 00:19:27.868
We must defeat the Knights
of Hanoi without his help.

00:19:38.812 --> 00:19:40.480
(Gore grunting)

00:19:45.019 --> 00:19:46.954
I need an ice down.

00:19:47.020 --> 00:19:48.956
Speed Duels really
make you feel the burn.

00:19:49.022 --> 00:19:50.357
(sighs)

00:19:53.727 --> 00:19:55.028
Thought I had that kid,

00:19:55.061 --> 00:19:57.397
but I couldn't kick out.

00:19:57.497 --> 00:20:00.066
Just gonna have to train harder
to win back my fans,

00:20:00.166 --> 00:20:02.603
especially my littlest ones.

00:20:02.670 --> 00:20:04.771
(child)
Hey, who you calling little?

00:20:04.838 --> 00:20:06.339
(children laughing, cheering)

00:20:06.440 --> 00:20:08.342
(girl)
You're the bestest ever, Gore!

00:20:08.375 --> 00:20:10.010
(boy)
And we're your bestest fans!

00:20:10.043 --> 00:20:13.047
You almost had him!
You'll win next time, right?

00:20:13.147 --> 00:20:14.982
(laughter continues)

00:20:15.015 --> 00:20:17.318
You'll always
be a champ to us!

00:20:17.351 --> 00:20:19.019
And here's the belt
to prove it!

00:20:19.052 --> 00:20:21.021
I got it down myself!

00:20:22.356 --> 00:20:24.391
So even though
I got my butt kicked,

00:20:24.491 --> 00:20:28.028
you're still cool that I went
from a hero to a zero?

00:20:28.061 --> 00:20:30.197
Cause this guy's feelings
won't get hurt

00:20:30.230 --> 00:20:32.032
if you don't want to see
anymore from The Gore.

00:20:36.003 --> 00:20:37.805
We want The Gore!
Take this belt

00:20:37.838 --> 00:20:39.640
and wear it like a champ,
but don't rip it.

00:20:39.674 --> 00:20:41.174
We're out of glue!

00:20:43.344 --> 00:20:44.645
I promise.

00:20:44.678 --> 00:20:46.313
Here you go.

00:20:46.346 --> 00:20:49.116
(children cheering)

00:20:49.183 --> 00:20:51.051
Ahh!

00:20:51.151 --> 00:20:53.486
(children laughing, cheering)

00:20:56.523 --> 00:20:58.491
(Gore laughing)

